{"id": "1391371818807460082", "channel_id": "1391371818807460082", "type": 0, "author_id": "197871477918269440", "author_name": "mac2492", "author_bot": false, "content": "Hameln's Descending Scale reduces the Arithmetica cost of the next Innate Command Card played by 2. When used with GRamona's Loop Sight Unbound (or Ramona's Exalt), the cards are displayed with their cost reduced by 2. Once played, the cost of the drawn card is not 0.\n\n<@736441008145039421> explained it as such:\nDescending Scale reduces Arithmetica cost by 2 until a card is played. \"Set cost to 0\" adds the current cost of the card to the cost reduction. Because the current cost is lower, the reduction is also lower. The cost is 0 upon draw but goes up when Descending Scale is removed. This happens immediately after playing Loop Sight Unbound. With Ramona exalt, you'll see the interaction if you play a card that isn't the one you chose.\n\nInstead of setting the cost reduction equal to the current cost, I think it should be set to max(original cost, current cost) in case the current cost is less than the original cost.\n\n------\n\nThese search skills might also have unintended interactions in the opposite direction since cost reductions can be higher than the cost of the card (this commonly happens with Prepare). If an effect is temporarily increasing a cost of a card by 2 then its cost reduction will also be increased by 2. If that temporary cost increase is removed, the card will cost 0 and will not go above 0 unless its cost is increased by more than 2.\n\ne.g. using Hameln's Ascending Scale with Ramona's Exalt sets the cost reduction to the card's cost + 2. when drawn, the card will cost 0. Ascending Scale can be used on another card and the searched card will still cost 0. if Ascending Scale is activated again, other cards will cost +2 but the searched card will still cost 0\n\nI can't think of a situation where this reverse situation would be a problem, but I figure it's safer to mention it just in case.", "timestamp": "2025-07-06T10:54:52.042000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-07-11T18:44:54.552000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": ["736441008145039421"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1391371819734536262", "filename": "IMG_3502.PNG", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 1708681, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1391371818807460082/1391371819734536262/IMG_3502.PNG?ex=6a0063fc&is=69ff127c&hm=27421fe9c4cab9f3844f3235c78c66a941598ff9799cf46b733159f6458dceda&"}, {"id": "1391371820254498877", "filename": "IMG_3503.PNG", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 3945144, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1391371818807460082/1391371820254498877/IMG_3503.PNG?ex=6a0063fc&is=69ff127c&hm=44da8117eddf6a95f2e63d5a3a3c45e813fb1644cc8d3a9bc41a9b8c5957a47a&"}, {"id": "1391371820955074643", "filename": "IMG_3505.PNG", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 2967527, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1391371818807460082/1391371820955074643/IMG_3505.PNG?ex=6a0063fc&is=69ff127c&hm=493764b942ca2e0e7a4d162d0b32d86d7c59c2d0bd555dbe3e064d8cae409afc&"}, {"id": "1391371821713985637", "filename": "IMG_3507.PNG", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 3630052, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1391371818807460082/1391371821713985637/IMG_3507.PNG?ex=6a0063fc&is=69ff127c&hm=f97ddb4c21e2ec73398c63cd1c51ae82229be39aa25f450e2f05e6890184fdbc&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1391371818807460082", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Hameln's rouse and searches that set cost to 0", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"]}
